Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with achieving the information-theoretic limit of quadratic multiple description coding, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper proposes a distributed source coding system, which can be applied in various network scenarios, such as wireless sensor networks and distributed storage systems. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance analysis of the proposed system under the high resolution assumption, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses lattice-based coding techniques, which are related to the design and analysis of efficient algorithms for lattice problems. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve some computational complexity analysis, as it deals with the performance of coding schemes under different distortion constraints.
